com.xilinx.rapidwright.design

Class SiteInst

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.SiteInst
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<SiteInst>

    public class SiteInst
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable<SiteInst>
    This class represents the instance of a site as configured by the user design. It can be part of a ModuleInst or part of a Design. It differs from the Site class in that it carries configuration data from the user design whereas Site is static and only represents available constructs in the silicon.
    See Also:

      • getSiteTypeEnum

        public SiteTypeEnum getSiteTypeEnum()
        Gets the type of the site instance (such as "SLICEL" or "SLICEM"). If the site instance type is set (through the constructor SiteInst), then that type will take precedence. If the site instance type is not specified in the constructor, the method will get the default type from its current site.
        Returns:
        The type of site for this instance or null if the type is not explicitly set or the site instance is unplaced.
        Since:
        2018.2.0

      • getPrimarySiteTypeEnum

        public SiteTypeEnum getPrimarySiteTypeEnum()
        Gets the primary site type (default type) for the site of this site instance. This is in contrast to other alternate site types (See Site.getAlternateSiteTypeEnums()) that can be applied to this site instance's site. The current site instance may or may not be configured with the primary site type.

        Vivado Tcl:

        get_property SITE_TYPE [get_sites $this]

        Returns:
        The primary site type for the site of this site instance.
        Since:
        2018.2.1
